We recommended that the City Mayor direct the:
Inventory Team to complete the physical inventory of all PPE;
City Accountant to coordinate with the City General Services Officer to address discrepancies between their records and prepare the necessary adjustments;
City General Services Officer to submit the complete inventory reports to the Auditor not later than January 31 of each year; and
City Accountant to provide details of the Construction in Progress accounts.

Conduct actual physical inventory-taking of the properties and prepare Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) be prepared and submitted;
Require the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain Property Cards, Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards for each category of assets, and Real Property Ledger Cards for land; and
Require them further to conduct periodic reconciliation of the ledger card balances in order to achieve accuracy and fair presentation of the financial statements.

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to post the Notice of Delinquency in the Payment of Real Property Tax and other taxes in a publicly accessible and conspicuous place in each barangay of the municipal government;
Also, to avail of the civil remedies provided for in Chapter IV, Title I, Book II of R.A. 7160 and develop other feasible strategies to enhance collections of delinquent taxes from taxpayers; and
To conduct periodic reconciliation of Real Property Tax Receivable with the Accountant and Assessor and to establish database for each individual Real Property Taxpayers.

We reiterated our recommendation that the City Mayor direct the:

a)	OIC-City Accountant to reconcile her records with the CCLDD, record the difference after the resultant effect of careful investigation, and maintain Subsidiary Ledgers for individual borrowers of livelihood loans for fair presentation of the Financial Statements;




b)	the OIC-City Accountant and the Head of CCLDD to exhaust all possible means to collect the outstanding loan accounts in order to improve collection efficiency and to prevent loss of government funds for the sustainability of the program.

observations.managementAction:
The LGU thru its newly elected officials, has initiated the designation of a permanent employee in addition to his actual job to focus on the recording of LGU’s PPEs;

The said personnel was accorded one set of desk top computer and printer;

The said personnel is presently gathering data and conduct initial physical inventory of the LGU’s PPE’s;

Encoding of PPE’s already assessed and determined is on-going.
Allowing said personnel to attend seminar on property and supply management to enhance his knowledge.

As to Fuel Consumption Utilization to be attached to individual voucher using fuels; it is fully implemented;

However, as to the submission of Monthly Report of Official Travel to the Auditor, the said requirement is not yet fully implemented since the person assigned to do such task is in doubt as to the forms and its contents to be submitted to the Auditor, whether copies of the travel order be submitted to the Auditor.

The LGU thereby request the Auditor as to the nature of the documents to be submitted to facilitate its submission starting the month of October 2016 and for accurateness.
